		<item>
			<title>Welcome to Quake2Lithium.com!</title>
			<link>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/47-welcome-to-quake2lithiumcom</link>
			<guid>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/47-welcome-to-quake2lithiumcom</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><br />Quake2Lithium.com is a fansite and international community dedicated to preserving the legacy of Lithium.&nbsp; Lithium is a server-side modification for Quake 2 created by Matt "WhiteFang" Ayres and released as open source in January 2010.&nbsp; Quake 2 Lithium is easily one of the fastest first person shooters ever released with unique gameplay including an off-hand grappling hook and runes (power-ups).&nbsp; See the action for yourself!&nbsp; Ready to play? Read our <a target="_self" href="https://quake2lithium.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=48&amp;Itemid=71">Quick Start Guide</a> and with a FREE download, you're all set to frag!<br /><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">{jumi [*11]}<br /><br /></div>]]></description>
			<author>admin@quake2lithium.com (Administrator)</author>
			<category>frontpage</category>
			<pubDate>Sat, 22 May 2100 12:11:12 +0000</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>All good things...</title>
			<link>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/84-all-good-things</link>
			<guid>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/84-all-good-things</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Nothing lasts forever, but Q2 and Lithium will live on in the hearts and minds of all that have played throughout the years.&nbsp; Though this will be the final update to this site, it will live on for archival purposes and migrated over to github in a static form.</p>
<ul>
<li>A static form of this site will be accessible @ <a href="https://quake2lithium.github.io">https://quake2lithium.github.io</a></li>
<li>Forum has been disabled permanently to support hosting on github.</li>
<li>All downloads on this site will live-on and be made available through github.</li>
</ul>]]></description>
			<author>admin@quake2lithium.com (Administrator)</author>
			<category>frontpage</category>
			<pubDate>Mon, 02 Apr 2018 15:55:34 +0000</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Lithium II v1.31 released!</title>
			<link>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/80-lithium-ii-v131-released</link>
			<guid>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/80-lithium-ii-v131-released</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><br />Matt "WhiteFang" Ayres has released v1.31 of his signature Lithium II Mod focusing on stability and bug fixes!!<br /><br /><strong>What is Lithium II?</strong> - Lithium II is a very configurable server-side modification for Quake II which includes deathmatch and CTF modes.&nbsp; Lithium II is well known for it's red-laser style off-hand grappling hook and runes.&nbsp; Have a closer look at the feature list <a href="http://quake2.lithium.com/features.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Download:</strong> <a href="https://quake2lithium.com//lithdownloads/viewcategory/5-lithium-mod" target="_self">here</a></p>
<p><strong>Changelog:</strong><br /><br />v1.31 - Sep 2010<br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />added, <a href="http://github.com/WhiteFang34/li2mod" target="_blank">source repository</a> to github<br />fixed, MOTD buffer overflow (from ralf)<br />added, use strlcpy/strlcat to protect against buffer overflows (from ralf)<br />thanks, ralf for all of the improvements, cleanup and updates for VC 2010<br />fixed, runes should be dropped for reuse if player goes into observer mode<br />added, don't repeat the same map if it was just voted on<br />added, time left to top of CTF scoreboard<br />fixed, rune spawning was broken if resist rune was disabled<br />fixed, safety couldn't be disabled by setting use_safety to 0<br />fixed, consistency of regen rune timing<br />fixed, chasecam mode didn't work if CTF was enabled<br />fixed, CTF flag was dropped from observers at level start<br />added, CTF flag return sound when it's returned for timeout<br />fixed, force CTF team menu after going into observer, chasecam or next map<br />added, muzzle logic to say_team command<br />disabled, lmaster support for now (and removed from docs)<br />thanks, again to d3s for facilitating this release!</p>]]></description>
			<author>admin@quake2lithium.com (Administrator)</author>
			<category>frontpage</category>
			<pubDate>Sun, 19 Sep 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Official Site Launch!</title>
			<link>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/55-official-site-launch</link>
			<guid>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/55-official-site-launch</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><br />Your one-stop site for everything Lithium related has been launched!&nbsp; We could say in a sense it's been 10+ years in the making, but better late than never! =)<br /><br />So, sit back, take your shoes off and take a test drive of our site.&nbsp; Come in and say hello on the forums, stop in our live chat room, and then go and download Quake 2!&nbsp; Don't forget that if you need any help getting started or reacquainted with the game, help is only a click or post away. </p>]]></description>
			<author>admin@quake2lithium.com (Administrator)</author>
			<category>frontpage</category>
			<pubDate>Fri, 16 Jul 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		</item>
